1
00:00:32,833 --> 00:00:34,460
- AC phase selector.
- AC.

2
00:00:34,501 --> 00:00:35,627
Force trim.

3
00:00:35,669 --> 00:00:36,829
On.

4
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:37,996
Battery switch.

5
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:39,164
On.

6
00:00:39,206 --> 00:00:40,764
Fire detector light.

7
00:00:40,808 --> 00:00:41,934
Test.

8
00:00:41,975 --> 00:00:43,499
Caution warning lights.

9
00:00:43,544 --> 00:00:45,512
Test and reset.

10
00:00:45,546 --> 00:00:47,480
By the way, congratulations.

11
00:00:47,514 --> 00:00:48,811
Have you thought of
a name for your kid?

12
00:00:48,849 --> 00:00:50,248
Well, we're still fighting.

13
00:00:50,284 --> 00:00:52,684
I'm holding out for
Joe DiMaggio Mazilli.

14
00:00:54,221 --> 00:00:55,688
The greatest Yankee
that ever lived!

15
00:00:56,690 --> 00:00:57,816
Hydraulic control switch.

16
00:00:57,858 --> 00:00:59,689
On.

17
00:00:59,727 --> 00:01:00,853
Lighting.

18
00:01:00,894 --> 00:01:02,020
In.

19
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:03,620
Heads up, guys.
Here comes Colonel Braddock.

20
00:01:03,664 --> 00:01:05,962
So, why would the colonel
want to go to Cambodia?

21
00:01:05,999 --> 00:01:08,490
Yeah, he could get hurt
going across the fence.

22
00:01:08,535 --> 00:01:11,003
He's leading a recon unit,
checking enemy strength.

23
00:01:11,038 --> 00:01:12,164
Clear?

24
00:01:12,206 --> 00:01:13,332
Clear left, sir.

25
00:01:13,374 --> 00:01:14,534
Let her rip.

26
00:01:17,378 --> 00:01:18,504
Main generator switch.

27
00:01:18,545 --> 00:01:19,671
On.

28
00:01:19,713 --> 00:01:21,647
- Turn switch.
- Fair.

29
00:01:21,682 --> 00:01:22,808
700 RPMs.

30
00:01:22,850 --> 00:01:24,317
Decrease.

31
00:01:24,351 --> 00:01:25,545
Good morning, sir.

32
00:01:25,586 --> 00:01:27,213
Good morning, Sergeant.

33
00:01:27,254 --> 00:01:29,313
Sorry I'm late.

34
00:01:29,356 --> 00:01:30,880
Would you like to take
the controls, sir?

35
00:01:30,924 --> 00:01:33,256
No, thanks, Captain.
I'm just along for the ride.

36
00:01:59,086 --> 00:02:01,350
What are the coordinates
on LZ Sally?

37
00:02:01,388 --> 00:02:04,551
Three-seven-four-zero-
three-zero-one-niner.

38
00:02:07,027 --> 00:02:10,019
We're right on top of them.
Let's give them a holler.

39
00:02:10,063 --> 00:02:12,623
Alligator four,
this is Red Gap six.

40
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:16,329
Alligator four, we're
taking fire from all quadrants.

41
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:19,806
Sir, they're in a fire fight
down there.

42
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:23,241
Charlie's got them pinned down
two miles south of the LZ.

43
00:02:23,277 --> 00:02:24,403
How bad is it?

44
00:02:24,445 --> 00:02:27,039
They're taking fire
from all quadrants, sir.

45
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:29,514
Do you want to go in?

46
00:02:29,550 --> 00:02:31,780
Hang on, guys.
We're coming down to get you.

47
00:02:31,819 --> 00:02:33,878
Get ready to move.
Take it down, Captain.

48
00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:51,463
Captain, let's move out now!

49
00:02:51,505 --> 00:02:52,802
Keep your shirt on, son.

50
00:03:25,038 --> 00:03:27,563
All right! Go!

51
00:03:31,678 --> 00:03:32,667
Come on!

52
00:03:38,952 --> 00:03:40,283
Come on, son.
We got to get out of here.

53
00:04:00,507 --> 00:04:02,668
Shit! Damn!

54
00:04:05,712 --> 00:04:06,838
You OK?

55
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:08,347
I'm fine.
Let's go to the chopper!

56
00:04:08,382 --> 00:04:09,542
Come on!

57
00:04:27,334 --> 00:04:29,302
Sir, they're getting
a good bead on us!

58
00:04:29,336 --> 00:04:30,325
Colonel!

59
00:04:31,905 --> 00:04:33,497
Looks like some
more party crashers, sir!

60
00:04:36,677 --> 00:04:38,110
All right, come on!
Get in there!

61
00:04:38,145 --> 00:04:39,806
Come on. Get in there. Quick!

62
00:04:42,149 --> 00:04:43,309
Sir!

63
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:44,510
Let's get the hell out of here!

64
00:05:00,968 --> 00:05:02,401
What the hell is that?

65
00:05:02,436 --> 00:05:04,836
We're hit! We're going down!

66
00:05:04,871 --> 00:05:07,101
I'm gonna try to make the lake.

67
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:08,129
Get ready to jump.

68
00:05:11,044 --> 00:05:12,136
Jump!

69
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:46,778
Jump, Lieutenant!

70
00:05:46,813 --> 00:05:48,405
I said, jump, Lieutenant!

71
00:06:29,289 --> 00:06:32,053
On the day America
remembers its war dead...

72
00:06:32,092 --> 00:06:36,324
a special salute today
to the war dead of Vietnam.

73
00:06:36,363 --> 00:06:39,821
An American serviceman who died
there took his place today...

74
00:06:39,866 --> 00:06:43,632
in a place of honor,
the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier.

75
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:47,333
Almost 10 years after the last
Americans left Saigon...

76
00:06:47,374 --> 00:06:51,105
the men who fought in Vietnam
got their parade.

77
00:06:51,144 --> 00:06:53,339
Muffled drums and dirges...

78
00:06:53,380 --> 00:06:55,940
a coffin and a flag
wrapped in plastic...

79
00:06:55,982 --> 00:06:57,950
to protect it from the rain.

80
00:06:57,984 --> 00:07:00,452
In the amphitheater
of Arlington Cemetery...

81
00:07:00,487 --> 00:07:03,012
families of the men
still missing from Vietnam...

82
00:07:03,056 --> 00:07:07,049
waited for the coffin
and remembered.

83
00:07:07,094 --> 00:07:10,029
They wonder if their sons
are still alive...

84
00:07:10,063 --> 00:07:11,758
and why the world sits back...

85
00:07:11,798 --> 00:07:13,356
and allows
the Vietnamese government...

86
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:17,166
to flagrantly violate
the Geneva Convention.

87
00:07:17,204 --> 00:07:19,638
Rumors of physical
and mental torture...

88
00:07:19,673 --> 00:07:22,107
have made
the wait more agonizing.

89
00:07:22,142 --> 00:07:26,306
The families were reassured
by a deeply moved president.

90
00:07:26,346 --> 00:07:29,543
We write no last chapters...

91
00:07:29,583 --> 00:07:31,744
we close no books...

92
00:07:31,785 --> 00:07:34,253
we put away no final memories.

93
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:36,949
An end to America's
involvement in Vietnam...

94
00:07:36,990 --> 00:07:39,458
cannot come
before we have achieved...

95
00:07:39,493 --> 00:07:43,827
the fullest possible accounting
of those missing in action.

96
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:14,449
Colonel Yin...

97
00:08:15,962 --> 00:08:19,591
you may not give a damn
about the Geneva Convention...

98
00:08:19,633 --> 00:08:23,262
but someday you're gonna
be held accountable.

99
00:08:23,303 --> 00:08:28,240
The Geneva Convention applies
to prisoners of war.

100
00:08:28,275 --> 00:08:31,711
You men are not
prisoners of war.

101
00:08:31,745 --> 00:08:34,043
You are common criminals.

102
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,672
I have repeatedly told you...

103
00:08:35,715 --> 00:08:38,343
that there is no escape
from my camp...

104
00:08:38,385 --> 00:08:43,049
unless you consider
death an escape.

105
00:08:43,089 --> 00:08:45,421
You are surrounded by cliffs...

106
00:08:45,458 --> 00:08:48,325
mountains,
jungles full of man traps...

107
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:51,853
and a bridge that is impassable.

108
00:08:51,898 --> 00:08:56,995
None of you have ever escaped,
and none of you will.

109
00:08:57,037 --> 00:09:00,996
The only way for you to leave
my camp...

110
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:04,670
is if Braddock confesses.

111
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:10,440
He defends the country
that has forgotten you...

112
00:09:10,483 --> 00:09:15,682
an outlaw nation
the rest of the world reviles!

113
00:09:21,528 --> 00:09:26,591
They are killing
your ambassadors of the evil...

114
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:28,396
in every part of the world.

115
00:09:49,723 --> 00:09:50,917
I have something for you.

116
00:09:56,630 --> 00:09:58,860
Hey, it's a beaut.

117
00:09:58,899 --> 00:10:00,161
It's a good two inches.

118
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,758
Angelo says thanks.

119
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:11,103
What he give you?

120
00:10:11,144 --> 00:10:13,237
A B-52.

121
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:15,043
It's just a worm
for his chicken.

122
00:10:24,324 --> 00:10:26,622
You know, I got to learn
to keep my mouth shut.

123
00:10:26,660 --> 00:10:28,719
What do you do?
You never shoot your mouth off.

124
00:10:28,762 --> 00:10:30,662
I try to decide
if what I'm going to say...

125
00:10:30,697 --> 00:10:31,857
is worth getting hit for.

126
00:10:34,401 --> 00:10:35,561
Wish I could do that.

127
00:10:35,602 --> 00:10:36,728
Franklin?

128
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:38,067
Hey, it's hot. I'm sweating.

129
00:10:40,073 --> 00:10:41,404
Looks like the malaria again.

130
00:10:41,441 --> 00:10:42,430
Hey...

131
00:10:50,951 --> 00:10:53,044
What the hell is Harry doing?

132
00:10:53,086 --> 00:10:56,214
I'll bite his head off
for a pack of cigarettes.

133
00:12:08,962 --> 00:12:10,429
Colonel Braddock,
I need to talk to you.

134
00:12:13,299 --> 00:12:14,288
Colonel.

135
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:23,703
Look, I'm real sorry
those two guys died...

136
00:12:23,743 --> 00:12:26,576
but we don't all have to.

137
00:12:26,613 --> 00:12:28,638
Maybe I can get Yin
not to ride you so hard.

138
00:12:28,681 --> 00:12:29,875
You'd like that,
wouldn't you, Braddock?

139
00:12:36,322 --> 00:12:37,653
How about it, Sarge?

140
00:12:37,690 --> 00:12:40,352
I mean, you know you could use
some time off.

141
00:12:40,393 --> 00:12:42,258
Begging the captain's
pardon, sir...

142
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:47,862
but kiss my black ass.

143
00:12:47,901 --> 00:12:48,890
That's funny.

144
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:51,828
All you guys are
big, brave soldiers...

145
00:12:51,871 --> 00:12:52,997
and you think I'm a coward.

146
00:12:53,039 --> 00:12:55,906
No, you're not a coward.
You're a traitor.

147
00:12:57,844 --> 00:12:59,004
I'm not a traitor.

148
00:13:00,747 --> 00:13:02,806
Look, our country
has forgotten about us...

149
00:13:02,849 --> 00:13:05,340
and we have to do
anything we can to survive.

150
00:13:05,385 --> 00:13:07,080
Look, I'm not the bad guy here.

151
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:09,748
It's Braddock
and his stupid pride.

152
00:13:09,789 --> 00:13:10,983
When we first got here...

153
00:13:11,024 --> 00:13:13,891
there were five times
as many of us... 33 Americans.

154
00:13:13,927 --> 00:13:14,916
Now look at us.

155
00:13:16,262 --> 00:13:18,059
I say that all Braddock
has to do is confess...

156
00:13:18,098 --> 00:13:21,124
to some garbage war crime,
and Yin will send us home.

157
00:13:21,167 --> 00:13:22,293
Who's gonna care?

158
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:25,331
The war has been over for...

159
00:13:28,541 --> 00:13:29,940
for God knows how long.

160
00:13:29,976 --> 00:13:31,341
We don't know that for sure.

161
00:13:31,377 --> 00:13:33,937
There is no war.

162
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:36,278
And nobody gives
a damn about us.

163
00:13:36,316 --> 00:13:38,477
Oh, yeah?

164
00:13:38,518 --> 00:13:40,383
Well, I hear they're
coming to get us.

165
00:13:40,420 --> 00:13:42,945
And if I were you,
I'd rather die here...

166
00:13:42,989 --> 00:13:44,354
than have to explain
to my kid...

167
00:13:44,390 --> 00:13:46,051
that I was a gutless traitor.

168
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:49,457
At least I've seen my kid.

169
00:13:51,064 --> 00:13:52,053
Let him go.

170
00:13:57,570 --> 00:13:59,003
Back off, Nester.

171
00:14:05,845 --> 00:14:07,779
Die if you want to, all of you.

172
00:14:15,355 --> 00:14:17,823
Who tell you someone coming?

173
00:14:17,857 --> 00:14:19,484
No one.

174
00:14:19,526 --> 00:14:21,357
I made it up to piss him off.

175
00:14:25,098 --> 00:14:27,123
Why'd those guys have to run?

176
00:14:27,167 --> 00:14:28,634
God, I got to get some sleep!

177
00:14:31,704 --> 00:14:34,229
But whenever I close my eyes,
I see my wife Gina.

178
00:14:38,945 --> 00:14:41,209
Yeah. My Diane's
gonna be mad at me.

179
00:14:43,416 --> 00:14:45,384
I wanted the four kids
more than she did.

180
00:14:47,187 --> 00:14:48,415
We made a deal.

181
00:14:50,557 --> 00:14:53,048
She'd work, and I'd retire
and bring them up.

182
00:14:56,529 --> 00:14:59,293
I fooled the hell out of her.

183
00:14:59,332 --> 00:15:01,197
I haven't even seen my kid!

184
00:15:08,408 --> 00:15:10,205
I'm sorry.

185
00:15:10,243 --> 00:15:12,177
I try to block it out,
but I can't.

186
00:15:12,212 --> 00:15:14,942
No one can.

187
00:15:14,981 --> 00:15:16,448
You do. Nothing bothers you.

188
00:15:18,017 --> 00:15:19,177
I'm just...

189
00:15:21,621 --> 00:15:23,452
I'm just not tough like you.

190
00:16:33,726 --> 00:16:34,715
Lao.

191
00:16:42,302 --> 00:16:45,100
Sergeant Lawrence Opelka...

192
00:16:45,138 --> 00:16:47,299
you have been tried
and found guilty...

193
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:50,867
of war crimes against
the people of Vietnam...

194
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:53,105
and have been sentenced
to death.

195
00:17:38,524 --> 00:17:39,684
Please!

196
00:17:45,965 --> 00:17:46,954
Nester.

197
00:17:49,836 --> 00:17:51,133
What does he want from him?

198
00:18:02,248 --> 00:18:03,510
Chou, get over here!

199
00:18:03,549 --> 00:18:05,608
Chou! You scum!

200
00:18:05,651 --> 00:18:07,642
Come down here, Chou!

201
00:18:07,687 --> 00:18:08,813
Mazilli!

202
00:18:08,855 --> 00:18:11,949
Come here, Chou!
You're nothing! Chou! Chou!

203
00:18:11,991 --> 00:18:14,687
You lose.

204
00:18:14,727 --> 00:18:15,989
You're scum, Chou!

205
00:18:16,028 --> 00:18:17,620
Get down here
and shut that door!

206
00:18:17,663 --> 00:18:18,789
Mazilli!

207
00:18:18,831 --> 00:18:20,992
Get down here, Chou!
I said, get down here!

208
00:18:21,033 --> 00:18:22,022
Mazilli!

209
00:18:24,337 --> 00:18:26,305
It's not doing anyone any good.
You know that.

210
00:18:26,339 --> 00:18:28,807
What the hell is going on?

211
00:18:28,841 --> 00:18:30,536
Why are they starting
this torture crap again?

212
00:18:42,522 --> 00:18:44,752
It's OK, kid. It's OK.

213
00:19:04,243 --> 00:19:06,177
Here. Brought you some things.

214
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:09,678
Did you get the quinine?

215
00:19:09,715 --> 00:19:11,910
No, I can't.
Yin has it locked up.

216
00:19:11,951 --> 00:19:15,284
But he told me to tell you
that if Braddock confesses...

217
00:19:15,321 --> 00:19:16,549
he will give it to you.

218
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:19,488
Yin can't be trusted.

219
00:19:21,661 --> 00:19:24,926
I've given him what he wanted,
and he's treated me well enough.

220
00:19:27,066 --> 00:19:29,125
He doesn't care about you.

221
00:19:29,168 --> 00:19:31,534
It's Braddock's confession
he's always wanted.

222
00:19:31,571 --> 00:19:34,540
Over the years,
it's driven him mad.

223
00:19:34,574 --> 00:19:37,134
Then why not
just give it to him?

224
00:19:38,544 --> 00:19:43,345
If Yin ever breaks Braddock,
we will all be killed.

225
00:19:45,685 --> 00:19:49,553
Colonel Braddock,
I have spoken to my superiors...

226
00:19:49,589 --> 00:19:51,386
and arranged for you
to be released...

227
00:19:53,159 --> 00:19:58,096
if you will simply let us film
your confession just once.

228
00:19:58,130 --> 00:20:01,588
No public appearances,
no questions.

229
00:20:01,634 --> 00:20:03,329
We could do it right now.

230
00:20:09,342 --> 00:20:10,639
You know I can't do that.

231
00:20:14,814 --> 00:20:19,342
Some of my men feel
I am being too lenient with you.

232
00:20:26,359 --> 00:20:27,451
Colonel Braddock...

233
00:20:28,794 --> 00:20:30,887
I didn't want
to have to tell you this...

234
00:20:30,930 --> 00:20:33,490
but maybe you should know.

235
00:20:33,533 --> 00:20:37,333
Your wife
is planning to remarry.

236
00:20:38,838 --> 00:20:41,204
She has you declared dead.

237
00:20:44,610 --> 00:20:46,840
Your family needs you.

238
00:20:50,182 --> 00:20:51,809
Sign this statement...

239
00:20:51,851 --> 00:20:55,787
I will let you go home
before the wedding.

240
00:20:58,524 --> 00:21:02,392
Colonel Yin, if my wife
is getting remarried...

241
00:21:02,428 --> 00:21:04,020
I'm happy for her...

242
00:21:04,063 --> 00:21:06,224
because if she's gonna wait for
me to sign this confession...

243
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:08,324
she's gonna be waiting
a long time.

244
00:21:17,777 --> 00:21:19,108
Get him out of here.

245
00:21:36,462 --> 00:21:37,622
Get down! Come on!

246
00:21:43,970 --> 00:21:46,165
Hey! Come on!

247
00:21:46,205 --> 00:21:49,140
That humper Lao is the biggest
asshole this side of Nester.

248
00:21:53,346 --> 00:21:55,576
Leave him alone, Lao.
You hear me?!

249
00:22:00,086 --> 00:22:04,216
Braddock, since you're
in a fighting mood...

250
00:22:04,256 --> 00:22:05,416
I'll give you one.

251
00:22:07,493 --> 00:22:10,394
Nester, you will be
Braddock's opponent...

252
00:22:10,429 --> 00:22:11,828
and you will win.

253
00:22:17,036 --> 00:22:18,264
I can't do that, sir.

254
00:22:20,506 --> 00:22:23,839
Colonel Yin, our deal was that
I would never have to hurt...

255
00:22:23,876 --> 00:22:25,275
any of the other prisoners.

256
00:22:26,812 --> 00:22:28,507
Fine.

257
00:22:28,547 --> 00:22:30,674
Don't fight.

258
00:22:30,716 --> 00:22:31,808
But...

259
00:22:34,286 --> 00:22:38,086
I will put you back
in the Americans' cell.

260
00:22:38,124 --> 00:22:42,618
I'm not sure you would be as
popular there as you once were.

261
00:23:06,018 --> 00:23:08,714
Why don't you just take a few
punches and go down, Colonel?

262
00:23:08,754 --> 00:23:10,483
