411
00:38:14,626 --> 00:38:15,888
Ho!

412
00:38:38,483 --> 00:38:40,644
Playboy, you want to play?

413
00:40:17,482 --> 00:40:18,506
You!

414
00:40:20,385 --> 00:40:22,785
I've been looking for you.

415
00:40:22,821 --> 00:40:24,118
About time you showed up.

416
00:40:24,155 --> 00:40:25,383
Your headquarters.

417
00:40:25,423 --> 00:40:26,822
You take me
to your headquarters.

418
00:40:38,870 --> 00:40:40,929
Name's Emerson... Clyde Emerson.

419
00:40:42,373 --> 00:40:43,863
No. You don't understand.

420
00:40:43,908 --> 00:40:46,308
Now, what is needed here is a
little courtesy and cooperation.

421
00:40:46,344 --> 00:40:49,541
I'm the point man for
a P.O.W. Search mission.

422
00:40:49,581 --> 00:40:52,982
The I.F.H. Got word of this
little operation some time ago.

423
00:40:53,017 --> 00:40:55,212
I must say, we've had
a devil of a time finding you.

424
00:40:55,253 --> 00:40:56,379
Who is "we"?

425
00:40:56,421 --> 00:40:59,151
Ah, yes. The International
Freedom House.

426
00:40:59,190 --> 00:41:02,023
I'm not just running around the
jungle looking for publicity.

427
00:41:02,060 --> 00:41:03,823
He lie.

428
00:41:03,862 --> 00:41:05,591
It's not a lie.

429
00:41:05,630 --> 00:41:07,325
I'm part of a major operation.

430
00:41:07,365 --> 00:41:08,798
There are nine other scouts
like me.

431
00:41:08,833 --> 00:41:11,597
We each have five square miles
to cover.

432
00:41:11,636 --> 00:41:14,867
And all of us call in
to Central Team regularly.

433
00:41:14,906 --> 00:41:19,036
Now, if you think that's a lie,
you are in a pack of trouble.

434
00:41:19,077 --> 00:41:20,203
Why don't you cooperate...

435
00:41:20,245 --> 00:41:22,440
and save yourself a lot
of needless bloodshed?

436
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:23,606
What the hell is going on?

437
00:41:25,250 --> 00:41:26,581
Damned if I know.

438
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:32,448
Do you really expect me
to believe you...

439
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:33,923
and turn over my whole camp?

440
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:36,889
Well, under
the circumstances, yes.

441
00:41:36,928 --> 00:41:38,793
I believe that's the only thing
that you can do.

442
00:41:38,830 --> 00:41:41,060
I hid a homing device
out there in the jungle.

443
00:41:41,099 --> 00:41:42,930
My team knows
exactly where I am.

444
00:41:42,967 --> 00:41:44,901
Now, they'll be waiting
for my signal.

445
00:41:44,936 --> 00:41:46,403
Now, if I give it,
they'll come in slowly.

446
00:41:46,437 --> 00:41:48,530
If I don't, they'll come in
fast, and you'll all be dead.

447
00:41:48,573 --> 00:41:50,040
What signal?

448
00:41:50,074 --> 00:41:51,439
Stop playing the fool.

449
00:41:53,244 --> 00:41:54,472
The way I figure it...

450
00:41:54,512 --> 00:41:58,209
these are your choices...
you can either cut and run...

451
00:41:58,249 --> 00:41:59,841
or you can wait
until my team comes in...

452
00:41:59,884 --> 00:42:02,409
and then you can try to run...

453
00:42:02,453 --> 00:42:04,614
or you can cooperate
right now...

454
00:42:04,656 --> 00:42:06,715
and save everyone
a whole lot of trouble.

455
00:42:12,497 --> 00:42:15,694
I believe you left out
some of my options.

456
00:42:15,733 --> 00:42:19,965
One, I could kill you
and the prisoners.

457
00:42:21,239 --> 00:42:22,763
Yes. Missed that one.

458
00:42:22,807 --> 00:42:26,971
And two... I can simply
lock you up...

459
00:42:27,011 --> 00:42:31,107
and wait until you're ready
to give the signal.

460
00:42:31,149 --> 00:42:32,673
Yes, you could lock me up...

461
00:42:32,717 --> 00:42:34,446
but I'll never give you
the signal.

462
00:42:34,485 --> 00:42:35,713
I don't care if you kill me.

463
00:42:35,753 --> 00:42:38,916
Now, look, I'm tired of
hanging around under this sun...

464
00:42:38,957 --> 00:42:41,482
playing footsie with
a half-pint would-be dictator.

465
00:43:01,346 --> 00:43:03,837
Give him anything he wants.

466
00:43:03,882 --> 00:43:05,008
I can't believe it!

467
00:43:05,049 --> 00:43:07,847
We're going home!

468
00:43:07,886 --> 00:43:11,344
OK. I want to know who won
the World Series last year.

469
00:43:11,389 --> 00:43:14,153
I don't know anything about
any bloody World Series, mate.

470
00:43:14,192 --> 00:43:15,318
I'm Australian.

471
00:43:15,360 --> 00:43:16,691
Forget it. I love you anyway.

472
00:43:20,965 --> 00:43:22,626
