499
00:44:25,296 --> 00:44:26,285
Well, move it!

500
00:44:30,468 --> 00:44:32,629
I'm just going to give
the signal, mate.

501
00:44:43,348 --> 00:44:44,815
Mr. Emerson.

502
00:44:44,849 --> 00:44:46,077
I'm just gonna give my signal.

503
00:44:46,117 --> 00:44:47,243
Good.

504
00:44:47,285 --> 00:44:48,752
Damn.

505
00:44:48,786 --> 00:44:51,448
I hope everyone's told you
how well they have been treated.

506
00:44:51,489 --> 00:44:52,820
Well, they don't love you,
but all in all...

507
00:44:52,857 --> 00:44:54,324
they look pretty good.
I'll be right back.

508
00:44:54,359 --> 00:44:55,849
One more moment, please.

509
00:44:58,463 --> 00:45:00,658
I would like you to meet
a friend of mine.

510
00:45:00,698 --> 00:45:02,632
I'll meet him later.
I'm in a bit of a hurry.

511
00:45:02,667 --> 00:45:04,999
I wouldn't want the Central Team
to get impatient, you know.

512
00:45:05,036 --> 00:45:06,230
Francois.

513
00:45:07,739 --> 00:45:11,300
What's the matter, my friend?
You look a little nervous.

514
00:45:11,342 --> 00:45:14,505
He is the goddamn guy who's
been asking questions about us.

515
00:45:14,545 --> 00:45:18,777
He claims he's the point man
for a major rescue operation.

516
00:45:18,816 --> 00:45:22,115
He's lying. He's alone.

517
00:45:22,153 --> 00:45:24,121
I've still got the homing
device out in the jungle.

518
00:45:31,262 --> 00:45:33,890
I am weary of playing footsie
with you.

519
00:45:36,467 --> 00:45:37,695
Take him to the tree.

520
00:45:40,972 --> 00:45:42,166
Move!

521
00:46:00,058 --> 00:46:04,051
For the crimes against
the people of Vietnam...

522
00:46:04,095 --> 00:46:05,995
I sentence you to death.

523
00:46:11,002 --> 00:46:13,232
Don't worry! It's not real!

524
00:46:13,271 --> 00:46:14,898
He's just trying to scare you!

525
00:46:14,939 --> 00:46:16,998
They've got
a lousy sense of humor.

526
00:46:32,457 --> 00:46:35,358
Get up. Get up.

527
00:46:36,761 --> 00:46:38,422
Shut up, you asshole.

528
00:46:38,463 --> 00:46:39,691
You...

529
00:46:39,730 --> 00:46:41,322
We'll get him up.

530
00:46:41,365 --> 00:46:42,423
OK, OK.

531
00:46:44,735 --> 00:46:46,464
I'm OK.

532
00:46:56,981 --> 00:46:57,970
Captain Ho?

533
00:47:16,167 --> 00:47:17,395
He's dying.

534
00:47:33,184 --> 00:47:34,173
Yin!

535
00:47:51,836 --> 00:47:53,394
No, don't do it.

536
00:47:53,437 --> 00:47:54,597
He has to.

537
00:47:57,275 --> 00:47:58,469
What the hell's the difference?

538
00:48:02,880 --> 00:48:05,678
Our struggle was a long one.

539
00:48:05,716 --> 00:48:09,015
As I predicted, you lost.

540
00:48:09,053 --> 00:48:15,617
I'm glad you finally understand
the extent of your guilt.

541
00:48:15,660 --> 00:48:16,957
You do, don't you?

542
00:48:16,994 --> 00:48:19,326
He don't understand shit!

543
00:48:24,001 --> 00:48:25,229
Yes, Colonel Yin...

544
00:48:27,038 --> 00:48:28,699
I understand.

545
00:48:43,454 --> 00:48:44,785
Let's get him up.

546
00:48:50,328 --> 00:48:51,556
Colonel Braddock.

547
00:48:54,365 --> 00:48:56,560
I believe you have
forgotten something.

548
00:49:14,252 --> 00:49:16,652
Now, my American P.O. W...

549
00:49:16,687 --> 00:49:20,384
I will live up to my promise
and will let you go free.

550
00:49:20,424 --> 00:49:24,485
Tomorrow, Francois will be here
and will fly you to Thailand...

551
00:49:24,528 --> 00:49:26,996
and deliver you to your embassy.

552
00:49:27,031 --> 00:49:29,056
You see, Colonel? I told you.

553
00:49:31,068 --> 00:49:33,195
I will try to make
your last day here...

554
00:49:33,237 --> 00:49:34,727
as comfortable as possible.

555
00:49:34,772 --> 00:49:39,038
Here. Come into the next room.
You'll stay there tonight.

556
00:50:03,134 --> 00:50:05,102
I can't believe it.

557
00:50:05,136 --> 00:50:06,865
It's over. We're going home.

558
00:50:06,904 --> 00:50:08,565
I'm going to see my kid!

559
00:50:09,974 --> 00:50:11,373
Something's wrong.

560
00:50:11,409 --> 00:50:12,603
Nothing's wrong.

561
00:50:12,643 --> 00:50:13,940
You've just been here too long.

562
00:50:13,978 --> 00:50:15,309
You're in shock.

563
00:50:15,346 --> 00:50:16,677
I am feeling better.

564
00:50:16,714 --> 00:50:17,874
Yeah, you're feeling better.

565
00:50:25,222 --> 00:50:27,087
Nothing works this fast.

566
00:50:29,627 --> 00:50:31,618
Oh, God! Get him up, Mazilli!

567
00:50:31,662 --> 00:50:33,220
He's been poisoned!

568
00:50:33,264 --> 00:50:35,425
Come on, Franklin!

569
00:50:35,466 --> 00:50:36,592
Come on, on both legs.

570
00:50:36,634 --> 00:50:37,760
Walk!

571
00:50:37,802 --> 00:50:39,497
- Come on.
- Walk, Franklin.

572
00:50:39,537 --> 00:50:41,971
Come on, walk it.
Walk, Franklin!

573
00:50:42,006 --> 00:50:44,133
Is this an American
funeral rite?

574
00:50:45,609 --> 00:50:52,481
I'm afraid I gave poor Franklin
such an overdose of opium...

575
00:50:52,516 --> 00:50:56,145
that he could walk
from here to Los Angeles...

576
00:50:56,187 --> 00:50:58,246
and would not do him any good.

577
00:51:02,026 --> 00:51:03,152
Throw him in the hole.

578
00:51:03,194 --> 00:51:05,185
You son of a bitch.

579
00:51:51,943 --> 00:51:53,240
Wait!

580
00:51:54,846 --> 00:51:58,373
Yin, wait!

581
00:51:58,417 --> 00:51:59,884
Yin!

582
00:52:03,789 --> 00:52:05,279
He's not dead!

583
00:52:09,094 --> 00:52:10,584
God, no!

584
00:52:10,629 --> 00:52:12,221
Oh, God!

585
00:52:19,004 --> 00:52:20,232
Son of a bitch.

586
00:59:09,881 --> 00:59:14,147
Mazilli, I thought
you should know...

587
00:59:14,185 --> 00:59:16,176
that you're completely alone.

588
00:59:16,221 --> 00:59:21,022
Your brave colonel has abandoned
you to die here.

589
00:59:21,059 --> 00:59:22,287
Braddock got away?

590
00:59:22,327 --> 00:59:23,794
He'll die tomorrow.

591
00:59:25,196 --> 00:59:26,356
So will you.

592
00:59:27,732 --> 00:59:29,063
In the meantime...

593
00:59:32,403 --> 00:59:34,234
if you're lonely...

594
00:59:37,475 --> 00:59:39,272
play with your friend.

595
01:00:03,067 --> 01:00:04,432
More wine, Colonel?

596
01:00:04,469 --> 01:00:05,458
No.

597
01:00:09,107 --> 01:00:10,836
Braddock gone!

598
01:00:10,875 --> 01:00:12,274
Why keep him alive?

599
01:00:14,179 --> 01:00:15,578
Now, you know,
I might be wrong...

600
01:00:15,613 --> 01:00:19,344
but I don't think it's
a very good idea to kill me.

601
01:00:19,384 --> 01:00:21,716
Why not?

602
01:00:21,753 --> 01:00:24,813
I could always get
someone to pour my wine.

603
01:00:27,992 --> 01:00:30,552
It's because
I'm the only one left...

604
01:00:30,595 --> 01:00:33,826
who really knows how
Colonel Braddock thinks.

605
01:00:33,865 --> 01:00:35,298
See, he hasn't gone yet.

606
01:00:37,836 --> 01:00:39,326
Is that so?

607
01:00:39,370 --> 01:00:43,238
Yes. He has stayed to try
and take revenge on you.

608
01:00:50,748 --> 01:00:53,273
I will use Francois' helicopter.

609
01:00:53,318 --> 01:00:55,013
We will capture him tomorrow.

610
01:00:59,123 --> 01:01:01,785
We should have killed that guy
a long time ago.

611
01:03:27,372 --> 01:03:29,067
We'd better get back.

612
01:03:29,107 --> 01:03:30,836
You'll never find
this guy alive.

613
01:03:30,875 --> 01:03:32,035
Just keep searching.

614
01:04:54,625 --> 01:04:56,525
Braddock come back,
blow bridge down.

615
01:04:56,561 --> 01:04:58,825
Lock up all the prisoners
and Nester!

616
01:04:58,863 --> 01:05:00,023
You, to the bridge!

617
01:05:03,801 --> 01:05:04,961
In there.

618
01:05:13,177 --> 01:05:15,145
I'll bury him with this.

619
01:05:18,082 --> 01:05:20,312
My God! It's a bomb!

620
01:05:20,351 --> 01:05:21,340
Get out!

621
01:05:30,428 --> 01:05:31,827
Damn American!

622
01:06:05,930 --> 01:06:07,056
Open it.

623
01:06:07,098 --> 01:06:08,087
Mazilli!

624
01:06:10,701 --> 01:06:12,032
What the hell?

625
01:06:12,069 --> 01:06:13,866
Braddock!

626
01:06:13,905 --> 01:06:14,929
Let's go!

627
01:06:17,375 --> 01:06:18,307
Duck!

628
01:06:23,614 --> 01:06:25,047
Come on! Come on!

629
01:07:13,397 --> 01:07:16,389
Damn! We got to find that rope.

630
01:07:22,173 --> 01:07:24,539
They're getting too close.
Let's get out of here.

631
01:07:24,575 --> 01:07:25,872
It's got to be here.

632
01:07:28,713 --> 01:07:30,203
Emerson said
they were under a big rock.

633
01:07:30,248 --> 01:07:31,613
There must be 60 big rocks.

634
01:07:36,420 --> 01:07:37,409
Here it is!

635
01:07:39,490 --> 01:07:40,479
Here.

636
01:07:55,039 --> 01:07:56,301
Good luck, kid.

637
01:07:56,340 --> 01:07:58,808
- Aren't you coming?
- I'm going after Ho.

638
01:07:58,843 --> 01:08:02,040
If you're staying to fight,
there's no way I'm leaving you.

639
01:08:02,079 --> 01:08:04,513
Here they come!
Get your ass down the cliff!

640
01:12:14,598 --> 01:12:15,929
You idiot!

641
01:12:23,140 --> 01:12:24,300
Come in.

642
01:12:26,010 --> 01:12:29,036
So, Yin, we're all loaded up.

643
01:12:29,079 --> 01:12:31,639
I'll see you in about a week.

644
01:12:31,682 --> 01:12:35,345
Francois, I will need
your helicopter...

645
01:12:35,386 --> 01:12:36,785
to look for the Americans.

646
01:12:36,820 --> 01:12:38,685
I believe they've gone down
the river.

647
01:12:38,722 --> 01:12:40,451
I am sorry. I can't help you.

648
01:12:40,491 --> 01:12:41,822
You will not go.

649
01:12:43,427 --> 01:12:45,725
I am going.

650
01:12:45,763 --> 01:12:47,196
Come on, let's go.

651
01:12:47,231 --> 01:12:50,667
Get your hands off...
What the hell are you doing?

652
01:12:50,701 --> 01:12:52,965
They are following my order.

653
01:12:54,305 --> 01:12:59,299
They needed a new leader after
they heard that you had died.

654
01:14:25,496 --> 01:14:26,485
Ho.

655
01:16:15,572 --> 01:16:16,766
Opelka.

656
01:16:16,807 --> 01:16:17,967
Colonel.

657
01:16:26,617 --> 01:16:27,982
I'm glad you made it, kid.

658
01:16:28,018 --> 01:16:31,317
Thanks, Colonel.
Yin must have given up on me.

659
01:16:31,355 --> 01:16:32,617
He thought you were dead.

660
01:16:34,358 --> 01:16:36,019
How come you hung around?

661
01:16:36,059 --> 01:16:37,219
I don't know.

662
01:16:38,695 --> 01:16:40,560
I guess it was just
some kind of instinct.

663
01:16:46,503 --> 01:16:48,903
I want you to guard the base.

664
01:16:48,939 --> 01:16:50,668
If I'm not back in 24 hours...

665
01:16:50,707 --> 01:16:52,436
go down the river
and try to find Mazilli.

666
01:16:54,711 --> 01:16:59,978
Colonel, I know you don't need
me to guard the base.

667
01:17:00,017 --> 01:17:02,247
I want to help you
get those bastards.

668
01:17:11,962 --> 01:17:13,122
Colonel Braddock!

669
01:17:25,542 --> 01:17:27,476
Yin's our enemy, too.

670
01:17:29,980 --> 01:17:31,140
I'll kill him!

671
01:17:32,549 --> 01:17:36,076
The fighting's over!
We all go home!

672
01:17:37,788 --> 01:17:38,914
Colonel Braddock!

673
01:17:38,956 --> 01:17:39,945
Dou Chou.

674
01:17:42,559 --> 01:17:44,220
He's listening.
He knows we're here.

675
01:17:53,237 --> 01:17:55,797
Yin dead. Believe now.

676
01:17:55,839 --> 01:17:57,739
See, Colonel Braddock?

677
01:17:59,309 --> 01:18:01,243
Come look for yourself.
Yin dead!

678
01:18:04,681 --> 01:18:07,115
Sir, the boots. That's not Yin.

679
01:18:22,466 --> 01:18:23,592
I'm going after Ho.

680
01:18:23,634 --> 01:18:25,329
He's in one of those two shacks
down there.

681
01:18:25,369 --> 01:18:29,328
If there's any fireworks,
here, throw these grenades.

682
01:18:30,774 --> 01:18:33,368
Sir, what about Nester?

683
01:18:33,410 --> 01:18:35,344
He can take care of himself.

684
01:18:35,379 --> 01:18:36,539
He always has.

685
01:18:40,617 --> 01:18:41,777
He won't show.

686
01:18:47,858 --> 01:18:49,018
He'll come.

687
01:19:09,079 --> 01:19:11,047
Good. They got Mazilli.

688
01:19:11,081 --> 01:19:12,070
Let's go.

689
01:19:29,566 --> 01:19:31,625
Colonel Braddock!

690
01:19:41,812 --> 01:19:45,441
I'll give you
30 seconds to decide...

691
01:19:45,482 --> 01:19:48,679
whether you want Mazilli
to live or die.

692
01:20:10,707 --> 01:20:12,902
Your 30 seconds is up!

693
01:20:14,277 --> 01:20:18,577
You have just murdered
your last man.

694
01:20:18,615 --> 01:20:21,083
Psst. Mazilli...

695
01:20:21,118 --> 01:20:23,348
anything you want me
to tell your kid?

696
01:20:26,223 --> 01:20:28,020
Hold it!

697
01:20:28,058 --> 01:20:29,355
Mazilli is mine.

698
01:20:31,328 --> 01:20:33,353
Why don't we just tell
the kid that Daddy...

699
01:20:33,397 --> 01:20:38,733
was a very brave soldier
right up till the very end?

700
01:20:43,774 --> 01:20:44,832
Down!

701
01:20:48,445 --> 01:20:49,742
Move it, Mazilli!

702
01:21:14,905 --> 01:21:17,237
Nester... he came back to us.

703
01:21:17,274 --> 01:21:18,263
Yeah, I know.

704
01:21:19,609 --> 01:21:20,769
I'm going after Ho.

705
01:21:42,632 --> 01:21:44,463
Cover us, Ho. We're going in.

706
01:21:53,643 --> 01:21:56,612
Colonel, they're all
in Yin's house.

707
01:21:56,646 --> 01:21:57,874
Opelka!

708
01:21:57,914 --> 01:21:58,903
Lieutenant.

709
01:22:03,787 --> 01:22:05,277
Opelka, left flank.

710
01:22:06,823 --> 01:22:09,451
Mazilli, around back.

711
01:22:09,493 --> 01:22:10,619
Wait.

712
01:22:10,660 --> 01:22:12,560
Ready? Go!

713
01:22:12,596 --> 01:22:13,893
Now!

714
01:23:51,761 --> 01:23:53,194
Nobody could have lived
through this.

715
01:23:55,131 --> 01:23:56,120
Colonel.

716
01:24:19,923 --> 01:24:21,413
Remember how to fly this thing?

717
01:24:21,458 --> 01:24:22,618
You better believe it.

718
01:25:26,256 --> 01:25:28,315
You really didn't think
I'd leave...

719
01:25:28,358 --> 01:25:30,019
without knowing for sure
you were dead?

720
01:25:33,096 --> 01:25:35,326
You'll not just kill me.

721
01:25:35,365 --> 01:25:38,528
You want to know
who the better man is.

722
01:25:39,869 --> 01:25:44,169
That is why you stayed behind.

723
01:25:44,207 --> 01:25:46,767
I also want to know.

724
01:25:46,810 --> 01:25:51,247
That is why I kept you alive
all these years.

725
01:25:54,551 --> 01:25:57,076
Now it is the time...

726
01:25:57,120 --> 01:26:01,250
You and I, one-on-one.

727
01:26:01,291 --> 01:26:02,451
No politics...

728
01:26:03,960 --> 01:26:05,450
no weapons.

729
01:26:14,270 --> 01:26:18,798
Just a little game to find out
who is the better man.

730
01:26:24,147 --> 01:26:27,116
I knew you could not
resist my challenge.

731
01:26:35,625 --> 01:26:39,061
Colonel Yin,
for the atrocities inflicted...

732
01:26:39,095 --> 01:26:41,825
on the Vietnamese and American
prisoners of this camp...

733
01:26:43,700 --> 01:26:45,668
I sentence you to death.

734
01:28:50,093 --> 01:28:51,492
This is for Nester.

735
01:29:00,870 --> 01:29:02,098
Not yet.

736
01:29:33,436 --> 01:29:35,301
The game's over.

737
01:30:12,008 --> 01:30:13,737
And this is for Franklin.

738
01:30:23,252 --> 01:30:24,583
You lose.

739
01:31:21,644 --> 01:31:22,804
This is for me.

740
01:31:32,805 --> 01:31:35,605
Ripped by:
SkyFury

